We have Nasolabial folds since childhood, but only as we age they start to appear as a thick fat folds extending from the wings of the nose to the corners of the mouth. They are one of the major aging signs on the face. When we smile our cheek and nose muscles become tense. Fat deposits move into the space where the tense muscles spasm creating thick fat folds called nasolabial folds. How do we treat, minimize and completely get rid of those folds? Many people choose fillers which are a temporary fix and have various consequences like tissue density which make those folds more profound and can further lead to formation of jowls. Only massage can release tension and relax tissues in that area, relocate fat deposits and soften nasolabial folds. Your rejuvenation lays in your hands!
